<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: W. LOS ANGELES; 
</P>
<P>
FUND-RAISING BIKE RIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nathan Reynolds, headmaster of the Westlake School for Girls, rode his bicycle 
across the country to raise $350,000 in pledges for the school's financial aid 
program. 
</P>
<P>
Reynolds, who celebrated his 56th birthday during the 3,150-mile trip from Los 
Angeles to Washington, has been the headmaster at the school at 700 N. Faring 
Road for 23 years. To prepare for the marathon trip, he followed a strict 
health and exercise regime that included 500 miles a week of early morning bike 
rides. 
</P>
<P>
The money raised from the tour will be used by the school's scholarship fund, 
which last year awarded more than $500,000 in scholarships to needy students. 
</P>
</TEXT>
