DIGEST: LONG BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
HARWOOD ADVOCATES MORE POLICE, NEW SUBSTATION EAST OF AIRPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Saying that Long Beach needs to expand its police force by more than the 10 
additional officers proposed in next year's budget, Councilman Warren Harwood 
is advocating the hiring of 45 new officers and the establishment of a police 
substation on the east side of Long Beach airport. 
</P>
<P>
Harwood, who intends to present his proposal at a budget hearing Tuesday, says 
his plan could be paid for with $3.2 million in new revenue from a variety of 
city fees, including airport and harbor fees. 
</P>
<P>
The city manager's proposed budget of nearly $1.3 billion includes funding for 
10 new officers, but the Long Beach police chief has said he needs another 164 
officers. 
</P>
