<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: SAN DIMAS; 
</P>
<P>
WATER COMPANY TO MOVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Southern California Water Co., which serves 10 San Gabriel Valley cities, 
is moving its corporate headquarters to San Dimas. 
</P>
<P>
The new building, under construction west of San Dimas Canyon Road between 
Foothill Boulevard and Baseline Road, will cost $4.5 million. When the building 
is completed in early 1990, 100 employees will move from the headquarters in 
Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
The company serves 255,000 customers in 61 cities throughout California, 
including Arcadia, Claremont, Covina, El Monte, La Verne, Monrovia, Pomona, 
Walnut, San Dimas and San Gabriel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
