<HEADLINE>
<P>
MICHIGAN HIGH COURT REJECTS PLEA ON ABORTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LANSING, Mich. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Michigan's Supreme Court refused Wednesday to rule on the constitutionality of 
a voter-passed ban on state payment for abortions ahead of the state Court of 
Appeals. In refusing to bypass the lower court, the justices said they were not 
convinced that the question needed to be decided so quickly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA060189-0171 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 64674 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
June 1, 1989, Thursday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part 2; Page 1; Column 6; Metro Desk 
