NEARBY COUNTIES FEEL 2 MILD QUAKES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two mild earthquakes rumbled through San Bernardino and Riverside counties 
early today, awakening some residents but causing no damage or injuries, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The first quake, measuring magnitude 3.5, struck at 2:33 a.m. near Redlands. 
Five hours later and 25 miles away, a magnitude 3.0 quake rattled the Crestline 
area, Robert Finn of Caltech in Pasadena said, adding that it wasn't known 
whether the temblors were related. The 7:23 a.m. quake, located 10 miles north 
of San Bernardino and 60 miles east of Los Angeles, was barely felt. 
</P>
