<P>
6 COLOMBIANS HELD IN COCAINE RAIDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Six Colombian nationals were arrested and $9-million worth of cocaine was 
seized during raids at five locations in Yorba Linda, Diamond Bar and Rowland 
Heights Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
Concluding a four-month investigation, deputies from the Los Angeles County 
Sheriff's Department, assisted by U.S. Customs agents and Montebello police, 
seized the 30 kilos of cocaine as well as $300,000 in U.S. currency, six 
vehicles and four cellular telephones during the raids, a sheriff's department 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Luis Velasquez, 36; Carlos Arbelez, 37; Juan Herrera, 24; George Cadavid, 27; 
Carlos Franco, 31, and his father, Antonio Franco, 66, were booked on suspicion 
of conspiracy to distribute cocaine. The six are being held in the Los Angeles 
County jail on $1-million bail each. 
</P>
